            <bug_when>2007-05-14 12:21:07 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>The tree view in the QxRunner GUI representing the tests could be coloured/icon changed according to test status (running/failed/success/etc.).

Status settings on individual tests could propagate up the tree hierarchy, to add the same tagging to parent nodes. This would allow the user to easily &#39;zoom in&#39; to failed tests from the root node (comparable with the little star that the Eclipse Source Navigator adds to all parent folders when a descendant file has changed).

The tree view could add a navigational means (e.g. buttons), to navigate to the previous/next node in the tree that has a non-successful tag, navigating across the hierarchical structure and selecting the respective nodes.

Selecting nodes in the tree could also update the Test Result tab view (if available), to focus/highlight the respective output.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
